<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4910457>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Beroe forskalii Milne Edwards, 1841. A, Entire specimen in stomodeal plane; B, same, aboral view; C, same, in tentacular plane; D, view of the aboral end in stomodeal plane; E, close-up of meridional canals and diverticula with male and female gonads; F, close-up of anastomosing diverticula near the mouth; G, close-up of the aboral end of the body. Abbreviations: adc, adradial canal; ao, apical organ; di, diverticule; fg, female gonads; ap, anal pore; mg, male gonads; mo, mouth; pa, papilla; pc, paragastric canal; pf, polar field; sscr, substomodeal ctene ro w; stcr, subtentacular ctene row; ssmc, substomodeal meridional canal; stmc, subtentacular meridional canal." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4910457/files/figure.png" .
